# Medallion-10: Iteration 16 — Re-attempt strapwork with symmetry-preserving crossing
#
# Iter 14 baseline (KEPT): composite=0.7842
# Iter 15 (strapwork width 5 alternating): composite=0.6604, REVERTED.
#   Failure mode: alternating crossings broke 10-fold symmetry
#   (A2 cv 0.067 -> 0.1325) AND fragmented voids into 185 unmatched
#   extras. Net composite -0.124.
#
# Mechanical edit: same strapwork block as iter-15 but `crossing over`
# instead of `crossing alternating`. The over-mode renders every
# strand-segment as an over-strand, making the over/under decision
# uniform across all crossings — preserves rotational symmetry exactly.
# Visually flat (no interlace illusion) but should keep A2 stable
# while still rendering bands (so A5 PARTIAL gain from iter-15 is
# preserved).
#
# Requires bikar PR1 (sacred-patterns/.claude/plans/bikar-symmetry-
# preserving-crossing.md) — adds `crossing over` and `crossing under`
# tokens. Built locally; not yet pushed to qiyas:dev image.
#
# Translation table mapping:
# - "iter 15 strapwork regression: A5 advanced one notch but A2 cv
#   doubled and 185 extras spawned" = use a symmetry-preserving
#   crossing mode instead of alternating.
#
# Predicted Δ vs iter 14 (NOT vs iter 15):
#   - A5: BROKEN -> PARTIAL preserved (~+0.03 svg-audit lift since
#     PARTIAL = 0.5 of 1.0 binary)
#   - A2: cv 0.067 (no degradation, since over-mode is rotation-invariant)
#   - extras: still spawn ~150-185 fragments, but the WARNING ranker
#     should now correctly attribute the regression to extras, not
#     to symmetry — informational signal for #109 (counterfactual tax)
#   - composite: vs iter-14 expect 0.74-0.79 (small dip from extras
#     dominates the small A5 lift; tax-aware warnings would have
#     predicted this)
#
# This iter is also a CONFIRMATORY EXPERIMENT for plan #108: does
# `crossing over` preserve A2 cv while rendering bands? If A2 cv
# stays under 0.08 we have proof that the new mode works as designed.

blueprint medallion
  circle C0 center(0,0) radius 100
  divide C0 into 10
  circle C1 center(0,0) radius 30
  divide C1 into 10
  circle Cmid2 center(0,0) radius 50
  divide Cmid2 into 10
  circle Cmid center(0,0) radius 80
  divide Cmid into 10
  repeat at C0 depth 1
    circle center($point) radius 0.3 * $radius
    divide into 10

pattern medallion on medallion
  layer 0
    connect every 4 on C1
    connect every 3 on C1

  layer 1
    connect every 4 on @0.0
    connect every 4 on @0.1
    connect every 4 on @0.2
    connect every 4 on @0.3
    connect every 4 on @0.4
    connect every 4 on @0.5
    connect every 4 on @0.6
    connect every 4 on @0.7
    connect every 4 on @0.8
    connect every 4 on @0.9

  layer 2
    connect every 3 on Cmid

  layer 3
    connect every 4 on Cmid2

  # NEW iter 16: same strapwork as iter-15 but with `crossing over`
  # to preserve 10-fold rotational symmetry. Renders all crossings
  # with the same over/under choice (uniform over-strands), which
  # is rotationally invariant.
  strapwork
      width 5
      crossing over

  voids detect

  palette medallion_blue
      deep_navy = #091428
      navy = #0D1B3E
      royal = #1B4F72
      cobalt = #2874A6
      turquoise = #48C9B0

  fill void where sides == 10 color deep_navy
  fill void where sides == 4 color royal
  fill void where sides == 3 color turquoise
  fill void where sides == 20 color navy
  fill void where sides >= 5 color cobalt

  edges color navy width 0.5
